title._content: Black High School Age Student At The Robert Taylor Homes, A Highrise Apartment Complex On Chicago's South Side, 05/1973

description._content: Original Caption: Black High School Age Student At The Robert Taylor Homes, A Highrise Apartment Complex On Chicago's South Side. He Is One Of Nearly 1.2 Million People Of His Race Who Make Up Over One Third Of Chicago's Population. It Is One Of The Many Black Faces In This Project That Portray Life In All Its Seasons. They Are Portraits Of Individual Human Beings Who Are Proud Of Their Heritage, 05/1973 U.S. National Archives’ Local Identifier: 412-DA-13696 Photographer: White, John H, 1945- Subjects: African-American Chicago (Cook county, Illinois, United States) Environmental Protection Agency Project DOCUMERICA Persistent URL: arcweb.archives.gov/arc/action/ExternalIdSearch?id=556148 Repository: Still Picture Records Section, Special Media Archives Services Division (NWCS-S), National Archives at College Park, 8601 Adelphi Road, College Park, MD, 20740-6001.
